# Git commit message format

Follow this style for every commit (see recent history on `Docs`). **Still require user confirmation before committing** (`submit-rule.mdc`).

## Subject line (first line)

- **Imperative mood**, concise, ≤ ~72 characters when possible.
- State **what changed** and, if obvious in one phrase, **why** (`Fix …`, `Add …`, `Move …`, `Clarify …`).
- Optional **scope prefix** in brackets for multi-module or tooling work:
  - `[VulkanDesktop]` — engine / `VulkanDesktop/` code or shaders
  - `[Cursor]` — `.cursor/rules`, skills, agent workflow
  - `[Docs]` — plans, progress, `SprintPlan.md`, `EngineArchitecture.md`
  - `[Lighting]` / `[Gfx]` — feature-specific when scope is narrow
- Small focused fixes may omit the prefix (repo uses both styles).

### Good subjects

```
Fix OBJ mesh load crash when UV coordinates are missing.
[VulkanDesktop] Add FPS fly camera with input snapshot and ImGui tuning
Move roadmap to Docs/SprintPlan.md and sync verification state.
```

### Avoid

```
fixed stuff
WIP
Update files
```

## Body (optional but preferred)

- Leave **one blank line** after the subject.
- **1–3 short sentences**: motivation, key mechanism, or verification note.
- Use bullets only when listing several independent changes.
- Do **not** paste `Co-authored-by` unless the user or tooling explicitly requires it.

### Example (full message)

```
[VulkanDesktop] Clarify contract comments and add comment rule.

Document UBO/descriptor bindings, queue-family fallback, and UV load guards.
Add cpp-comments.mdc; link from layout and vibe-coding-entry rules.
```

## When closing Docs workflow tasks

- Mention plan/progress or `SprintPlan.md` in the body if the commit completes a tracked item.
- **Move the completed line to `## Archived`** in `Docs/SprintPlan.md` (tag sprint, e.g. `[S1]`); active sprints must not keep `[x]` items.
- Prefer one logical change per commit (matches recent maintenance commits).
- If a session delivers **both** a sprint plan task **and** a separate policy/shader fix (e.g. resource tables + push-constant `model`), use **two commits** when history clarity matters; reference both in `_Progress.md`.
